HEADWORD: Rhizopoda
<hw>Rhi*zop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/<?/<?/ a root + <ets>-poda</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An extensive class of Protozoa, including those which have
pseudopodia, by means of which they move about and take their food. The
principal groups are Lobosa (or Am⟦oe⟧bea), Helizoa, Radiolaria, and
Foraminifera (or Reticularia). See <er>Protozoa</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhizopodous</ent>⟦br⟧
